147
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:23,050
What do you think will happen

148
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:24,530
when that debt bubble bursts?”

149
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:26,500
Good question, Timothy.

150
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:28,950
Yes, China does have a little bit of debt.

151
00:06:28,950 --> 00:06:32,050
Like, around 10 trillion dollars worth.

152
00:06:32,050 --> 00:06:33,450
And that’s just national debt.

153
00:06:33,450 --> 00:06:37,470
It doesn’t included an additional 6 trillion
in local debt

154
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:39,750
that doesn’t usually get counted.

155
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:40,750
Which does make me feel

156
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,840
slightly better about my student loans.

157
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:45,730
A lot of local debt goes to finance things
like,

158
00:06:45,730 --> 00:06:47,730
I don’t know, skyscrapers!

159
00:06:47,730 --> 00:06:48,770
But in modern economies,

160
00:06:48,770 --> 00:06:52,500
debt doesn’t necessarily mean imminent economic
collapse.

161
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:55,130
The US has even more national debt than China,

162
00:06:55,130 --> 00:06:58,730
and our economy is probably not in any serious
bubble.

163
00:06:58,730 --> 00:07:00,830
Will China have a financial crisis?

164
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:02,810
Probably yes, at some point.

165
00:07:02,810 --> 00:07:04,530
But it’s impossible to predict when,

166
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:06,650
or what event will knock over the first domino.

167
00:07:06,650 --> 00:07:09,270
It could be the bursting of the real estate
bubble.

168
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,270
And if that happens,

169
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:13,000
China’s economy might end up looking like
this.

170
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,000
Or this.

